    "biography": "SZA (Solána Imani Rowe) is a global icon reshaping the landscape of modern music. SZA has become a defining artist of her generation; born in St. Louis and raised in New Jersey. She first captured the world’s attention with her groundbreaking debut album Ctrl (2017), in which she earned acclaim for blending vulnerability with genre-blurring melodies. In 2022, her chart-topping sophomore album SOS pushed boundaries, and its deluxe edition, SOS Deluxe: LANA (2024), solidified her place among music’s greats with 15 new tracks showcasing her evolution.\n\nFrom Grammy wins to sold-out tours and iconic collaborations with Kendrick Lamar, Doja Cat, and Travis Scott, SZA continues to inspire and connect deeply with fans worldwide through her music about love, self-discovery, and empowerment."
