    "biography": "Imagine Dragons continue to redefine rock in the 21st century. Filling stadiums, crafting cloud-rattling anthems, &amp; breaking records at every turn, diamond-certified GRAMMY Award-winning band Imagine Dragons occupy rarified air as one of the biggest rock bands in the world. Tallying cumulative sales of 74M&#43; album equivalents, 65M&#43; digital songs, &amp; over 160 billion streams, they stand out as “the only band in history to earn four RIAA Diamond singles. Since emerging in 2009, they’ve scored five consecutive Top 10 debuts on the Billboard Top 200 with Night Visions [2012] (7x-platinum), Smoke&#43;Mirrors [2015] (platinum), Evolve [2017] (triple-platinum), Origins [2018] (platinum), &amp; Mercury – Act 1 [2021] (platinum). Dominating radio, they remain one of only four bands to achieve consecutive Top 5 singles at Alternative radio, &amp; the only band to repeat this feat. The band holds the crown for the group with most billion-plus streamed songs on Spotify, becoming the first in the platform’s history to have ten songs reach this milestone. They’ve collaborated with everyone from Kendrick Lamar, Lil Wayne, Wiz Khalifa, Avicii &amp; film composer Hans Zimmer. Giving back, they’ve raised millions for various causes, including their pediatric cancer charity (Tyler Robinson Foundation), &amp; frontman Dan Reynolds&#39; LOVELOUD Foundation &amp; festival in support of LGBTQ&#43; youth. In 2022, Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelensky named them ambassadors for UNITED 24, which benefits humanitarian aid in Ukraine"
